Mavin Records signee, Ladipoe has explained what necessitated the switch from his former stage name Poe. Born Ladipo Eso, the rapper in an interview with Cool FM’s Kemi Smallz, stated the name change was to avoid copyright infringement According to the father of one, his song “Man already” released in 2017 was being showcased in the discography of an American folk songstress whose name was equally Poe. He said he was contacted by her legal team to either change his name of risk legal action, making him switch to Ladipoe, which coined from his original name. “In 2017, going to 2018, I released a song, “Man Already”. I didn’t even realise the song was already on Spotify but it was on another Poe’s Spotify. And this Poe was actually a folk singer in the US.   Actor Alexx Ekubo hails Tacha’s versatility     I want to perform ‘Buga’ at World Cup –…     Davido gives Ghanaian with ‘A1 parallel’ varsity scholarship   “Promptly after we released “Man Already”, some months after, we got an email from their lawyer saying they were either gonna take action or I changed my name. “And TuneCore was like, ‘Yeah you have those two options. Either we take your music down or change your name.’ “Ladipoe just made so much sense, so around 2017/2018, that’s when the name changed. And it’s been Ladipoe ever since then. “Although, my close friends since call me Poe but officially now, on all music platforms, it’s Ladipoe,” he said. Attachments area